For allegedly raping a minor, one Kehinde Odunlade, (27) was on Monday docked at an Osun State Magistrates’ Court sitting Ile-Ife. Odunlade however, pleaded not guilty to the two-count charge of conspiracy and indecent assault levelled against him. The police prosecutor, Inspector Sunday Osanyintuyi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Dec 22, 2019 around 10:00 am at Igboya Area, Ile-Ife. He noted that the defendant conspired among themselves to commit felony to wit: Indecent assault. He added that the defendant unlawfully and indecently assaulted 15-year-old minor, (name withheld). According to him, the offence contravened sections 360 and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun, 2002. The Defence Counsel, Mr Olurotimi Oyebuade, applied for the bail of the defendant in most liberal term. He pledged that his client would not jump bail, but would stand his case and produce reliable sureties. Magistrate Muhibah Olatunji granted the bail of the defendant in the sum of N500,000 with two sureties. Olatunji said the sureties must swear to affidavit of means, resides within the court jurisdiction and be a civil servant of not below Level 10 salary scale among other bail conditions as adjourned the case until Feb 10, for hearing. 